{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"c796d05d-8deb-489d-bb95-495b5376558a","title":"Security","vault":{"fsPath":"programming","name":"programming"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"ref","from":{"fname":"programming.javascript.node-js.security","id":"c796d05d-8deb-489d-bb95-495b5376558a","vaultName":"programming"},"value":"networking.nginx","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":374},"end":{"line":19,"column":54,"offset":427},"indent":[]},"xvault":true,"to":{"fname":"networking.nginx","anchorHeader":"conclusion","vaultName":"networking"}}],"anchors":{"avoid-80-port":{"type":"header","text":"Avoid 80 port","value":"avoid-80-port","line":8,"column":0},"why":{"type":"header","text":"Why?","value":"why","line":13,"column":0},"what-is-the-main-problem":{"type":"header","text":"What is the main problem?","value":"what-is-the-main-problem","line":17,"column":0},"aditional-information":{"type":"header","text":"Aditional information","value":"aditional-information","line":27,"column":0}},"fname":"programming.javascript.node-js.security","updated":1621708730548,"created":1621708493720,"parent":"dec2b4d3-ff94-4735-8797-0a65986de197","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"bfa80d671798e325abe9e612ae7f6b65","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"security\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#security\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Security</h1>\n<h2 id=\"avoid-80-port\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#avoid-80-port\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Avoid 80 port</h2>\n<p>Avoid running our Node.js app on port 80\nIn most cases is not a good idea to start our app on port 80.</p>\n<h3 id=\"why\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#why\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Why?</h3>\n<p>On linux environments root access is needed to use the ports &#x3C;= 1024</p>\n<h3 id=\"what-is-the-main-problem\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#what-is-the-main-problem\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>What is the main problem?</h3>\n<p>We are exposed, attackers can find the way to run commands for them using root privileges.</p>\n<p>Posible Solutions:</p>\n<p>A reverse proxy like nginx</p>\n<p></p><p></p><div class=\"portal-container\">\n<div class=\"portal-head\">\n<div class=\"portal-backlink\">\n<div class=\"portal-title\">From <span class=\"portal-text-title\">Nginx</span></div>\n<a href=\"/notes/5eb04dc2-7759-4fa7-845a-48043ffe2382\" class=\"portal-arrow\">Go to text <span class=\"right-arrow\">â†’</span></a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"portal-parent-anchor\" class=\"portal-parent\" markdown=\"1\">\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-top\"></div>\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-bottom\"></div><h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#conclusion\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>NGINX: Definitely solve more of the issues regarding to security, cache, ssl, load balancing, reverse proxy and so on. Is a great option to be used combined with PM2 or Cluster Module</p>\n<h2 id=\"aditional-information\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#aditional-information\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Aditional Information</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/mzavaletavargas/going-live\">https://github.com/mzavaletavargas/going-live</a></p>\n</div></div><p></p><p></p>\n<h1 id=\"aditional-information-1\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#aditional-information-1\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Aditional information</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.nikola-breznjak.com/blog/javascript/nodejs/using-nginx-as-a-reverse-proxy-in-front-of-your-node-js-application/\">http://www.nikola-breznjak.com/blog/javascript/nodejs/using-nginx-as-a-reverse-proxy-in-front-of-your-node-js-application/</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16770673/using-node-js-only-vs-using-node-js-with-apache-nginx\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16770673/using-node-js-only-vs-using-node-js-with-apache-nginx</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/node/comments/2rjsty/why_not_run_on_port_80/\">https://www.reddit.com/r/node/comments/2rjsty/why_not_run_on_port_80/</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.risingstack.com/node-js-security-tips/\">https://blog.risingstack.com/node-js-security-tips/</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16573668/best-practices-when-running-node-js-with-port-80-ubuntu-linode\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16573668/best-practices-when-running-node-js-with-port-80-ubuntu-linode</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://hashnode.com/post/10-things-you-shouldnt-do-while-running-nodejs-in-production-cisab2fyu0s9oth5341faywcw\">https://hashnode.com/post/10-things-you-shouldnt-do-while-running-nodejs-in-production-cisab2fyu0s9oth5341faywcw</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"23f9dc67-8303-4034-90d3-7371e6cc8996","title":"Welcome","vault":{"fsPath":"vault","name":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"ref","from":{"fname":"root","id":"23f9dc67-8303-4034-90d3-7371e6cc8996","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"architecture.microservices","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":460},"end":{"line":14,"column":55,"offset":514},"indent":[]},"xvault":true,"to":{"fname":"architecture.microservices","vaultName":"architecture"}}],"anchors":{"personal-wiki":{"type":"header","text":"Personal wiki","value":"personal-wiki","line":8,"column":0},"content-example":{"type":"header","text":"Content Example","value